lliam was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705183,"age":36,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Ingeram was born about 1050, in England, his father, William de Ingeram, was 32 and his mother, Mrs William de Ingeram, was 23. He married Miriam before 1075, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1090, in his hometown, at the age of 42."},"et":{"about 1050–about 1090":"umbes 1050–umbes 1090","1050–1090":"1050–1090","1060–1080":"1060–1080","1075–1130":"1075–1130","1020–Male":"1020–Surnud","1029–Female":"1029–Surnud","about 1050":"umbes 1050","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","about 1090":"umbes 1090","about 1080":"umbes 1080","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1020":"1020","1130":"1130","1075":"1075","1050":"1050","1060":"1060","1029":"1029","before 1075":"enne 1075","about 1075":"umbes 1075","Ayresome, Yorkshire, England":"Ayresome, Yorkshire, England","Europe":"Europe","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1050–about 1090":"noin 1050–noin 1090","1050–1090":"1050–1090","1060–1080":"1060–1080","1075–1130":"1075–1130","1020–Male":"1020–Kuollut","1029–Female":"1029–Kuollut","about 1050":"noin 1050","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","about 1090":"noin 1090","about 1080":"noin 1080","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1020":"1020","1130":"1130","1075":"1075","1050":"1050","1060":"1060","1029":"1029","before 1075":"ennen vuotta 1075","about 1075":"noin 1075","Ayresome, Yorkshire, England":"Ayresome, Yorkshire, England","Europe":"Eu